  {
    "tag": "tscircuit/core#2305",
    "number": 2305,
    "title": "Fix jlcpcb CAD fallback for library footprints",
    "description": "Fixes 3D rendering for library footprints that do not provide a CAD model by falling back cleanly to a bounding box instead of surfacing a parser error.",
    "contributor": "techmannih",
    "repo": "tscircuit/core",
    "url": "https://github.com/tscircuit/core/pull/2305",
    "mostly_style": false,
    "new_page_or_component": false,
    "introduces_or_fixes_a_footprint": true,
    "core_change": true,
    "only_dependency_update": false,
    "bad_title": false,
    "introduces_new_circuit_board": false,
    "fixes_circuit_board": false,
    "fixes_subtle_important_bug": true,
    "minor_fix": false,
    "major_autorouter_bug_fix": false,
    "only_adds_autorouter_fixtures": false,
    "only_reproduces_a_bug": false,
    "reproduces_and_fixes_a_bug": false,
    "minor_developer_experience_improvement": false,
    "major_experience_improvement": false,
    "introduces_new_schematic_symbol": false,
    "fixes_schematic_representation": false,
    "improves_parts_engine": false,
    "add_design_to_schematic_corpus": false,
    "major_improvement_to_core_data_modeling": false,
    "major_library_algorithm_contribution": false,
    "substantially_improves_svg_generation": false,
    "user": {
      "login": "techmannih"
    },
    "html_url": "https://github.com/tscircuit/core/pull/2305",
    "created_at": "2026-05-16T20:21:33Z",
    "merged_at": "2026-05-20T17:07:58Z",
    "body": "## What changed\nThis updates CAD fallback generation for library-style footprints so `cad_component.footprinter_string` is only emitted for direct footprinter strings such as `0402` or `soic8`.\n\nFor library references like `jlcpcb:C51950748`, KiCad library refs, URLs, and static asset paths, the fallback now emits a bounding-box CAD component instead of forwarding the library reference as a footprinter string.\n\n## Why this changed\nThe 3D viewer was trying to parse `jlcpcb:...` as a raw footprinter function when no CAD model was available. That produced runtime errors like:\n\n`Invalid footprint function, got \"jlcpcb\"`\n\nThe underlying footprint could still load for PCB rendering, but the CAD fallback path was sending an invalid string into the 3D engine.\n\n## Impact\nThis fixes 3D rendering for library footprints that do not provide a CAD model by falling back cleanly to a bounding box instead of surfacing a parser error.\n\n## Root cause\n`NormalComponent.doInitialCadModelRender()` treated any string footprint as a valid `footprinter_string` fallback. Library refs such as `jlcpcb:...` are valid footprint lookup keys, but they are not valid raw footprinter expressions.\n\n## Validation\n- `bun test tests/footprint/footprint-library-map-jlcpcb-cadmodel.test.tsx`\n- `bun test tests/components/normal-components/cad-component-bounding-box.test.tsx`\n\n## Notes\nRepo-wide build/type generation still has unrelated pre-existing DTS failures in `lib/components/primitive-components/PcbTrace.ts`.\n",
    "state": "merged",
    "isAlignedWithMilestone": false,
    "starRating": 2,
    "impact": "Minor"
  },
